des:
The Municipal Archaeological Museum of Cabra possesses archaeological pieces representative of the region and of the municipal term itself. In the courtyard of the Casa de la Cultura are exhibited paleontological and archaeological remains of various periods: Palaeolithic, Epipaleolithic, Chalcolithic, Bronze, Colonizations, Iberian Culture, Roman, Hispano-visigothic, Hispanic-Muslim, Modern and contemporary.
Among the pieces deposited in this museum space are Roman sculptures such as a carving of a sleeping Eros, an image of Dionysus and a replica of a unique example of the divinity of the Mithra Tauroctonos, whose original is in the Provincial Archaeological Museum of Cordoba.
